text:
a friend of mine was recently violated. a friend of mine went on a date and trusted she would make it home safe; she believed a man who promised to keep his distance. a friend of mine was wrong. a friend of mine struggled and fought for 40 minutes before she was finally able to escape. a friend of mine blames herself for all the wrong reasons. a friend of mine is struggling with depression and anxiety as her body processes the trauma and as the criminal justice system processes her. a friend of mine is using the punishing winds of winter hikes to externalize all the pain and anger inside. a friend of mine was raped. and she wishes coming out as a survivor was as easy as coming outdoors for healing.
.
to all you silent warriors out there, keep fighting. we will know your name by the defiance in your strut.
.
.
note: the panunkey, piscataway, and other #native tribes originally lived in and traveled through the land that is now rock creek national park. .
.

text:
we want to achieve a safe place for those, past and present, who have been affected by assault and harassment, directly and indirectly. we want people to know we are there if they want any kind of support that is not of an authoritive figure, to talk and give advice to people regarding their situations or simply just be friends. there is no pressure to talk about anything that you do not feel comfortable talking about. 
not everyone is lucky enough to know someone who has been through a similar situation, who can give advice and emotional support, so this group offers that both online and in person.

painting on board 90x130

maria callas was a person who give me a lot of emotion and admiration. she herself was creating her own character and this ended up transforming her into her life as a diva. she was the creator of herself, marking a glamorous time and leaving an artistic legacy that for now no one has overcome her voice. the diva could not miss in my collection of paintings, i wanted to have her presence and her energy with me and it was a exquisitely pleasure to be able to paint her.

the self-described introvert says her dream, girl screening planted seeds that allowed her to take big steps, both personally and professionally. “it had a massive impact in so many different ways,” naomi said. “it gave me confidence and allowed me to see that i could actually pull that off and people could leave feeling good.” #womeninfilm #startupstory #startupcommunity #girlbossmagic #girlbossquotes #feministquotes #feministmovement #feministartist #femalefilmmaker #femalefilmmakers #femalefilmmakerfriday #ceos #ceomom #meditatedaily  #dreamerswelcome #dreamersunite #dreamerforever #metoo #timesup #supersoul #supersoulconversations #supersoul100 #dreamgirlfilm

text:
you are the sun 🌞 
for them to see you shine, you must stay far away, for you’re just like the sun; when you’re too close, your light makes them blind. and when you’re too far, they seek you. so let them seek you. 
they’re getting your light regardless, but appreciating your presence is different from recognising your existence.

text:
hola gente,
it’s time to talk about women in the workforce! inspiration for this episode came from the #metoo and time’s up movement. alex maestre, a field engineer who puts in hard work at construction sites, joins us today and swaps stories with ashley about their experiences being a woman in male-dominated careers. 〰️
today we cover:
✖️sexism
✖️can women be sexist
✖️advantages and privileges
✖️sexual harassment
〰️
here at la gente podcast, we want nothing but for all genders, races, and etc to be treated as equals. let’s all start by making sure women are safe because without them we would not exist!
-la gente podcast

text:
after the absolutely disgusting use of a victim’s underwear to justify a rape case, and her subsequent suicide, there’s an important message that some people in society need to accept 
these are the pants i wore the day i was raped - are they lacy? yes. do they show off a bit of skin? yes. when i put them on did i think ‘ah do these act as a form of content?’ no. 
words are consent, wilful actions are consent. saying yes is consent. 
stop. blaming. victims. 
#metoo #metoomovement #thisisnotconsent #consent #rapevictim #rapeawareness #rapeculture

text:
ein roman, eine geschichte - das ist glück dich! auf jeden fall. aber noch viel mehr, ein statement. und das zeigt ihr mit euren mutigen geschichten und entscheidungen. 
glück dich! wirft fragen auf 
seid ihr glücklich? wo und warum seid ihr festgesteckt und musstet eine schwere entscheidung treffen? wo übernehmt ihr schon die verantwortung für euer glück? und: braucht es immer einen traumprinz, um glücklich zu sein?
ein schwieriges thema spricht glück dich! auch an: sexuelle belästigung #metoo - und eure antworten dazu sind so krass ehrlich, waren sehr ernüchternd - und leider auch ein dringendes signal, dass sich was ändern muss.
tolle antworten haben diese tollen instagrammer & bücherverrückten gefunden - zum teil gibt es auch gewinnspiele!!!! guckt mal!

the oxford dictionaries has been chosen “toxic” as its ‘word of the year 2018’. traditionally, the word “toxic” has been used to describe harmful chemical substances e.g. toxic waste and toxic gas. the dictionary defines “toxic” as “poisonous” with its roots derived from the medieval latin term “toxicus,” meaning poisoned or imbued with poison. but, it has recently developed wider social meanings in light of the #metoo movement and the increasingly volatile political landscape fostered by the brexit vote.

text:
#jedertaghatwasschönes #fuckdepression #nevergiveuplive🌞 #mentalhealth #metoo #musiktherpie #icare #iamthechange #320changesdirektion
hallo ihr lieben,so langsam geht es wieder bei mir. oder vielleicht auch eher nicht..es ist alles sehr verwirrendund ich komme mit der neuen situation nicht zurecht. kurz zusammengefasst: ich weiß jetzt seit14 tagen woher meine probleme kommen. ich musste es mir hart erarbeiten, denn die ursacheliegt fast 25 jahre zurück. ich hatte damals einen freund, der mich psychisch und physisch wehgetan hat..mich eingesperrt hat, sexuell unter druck gesetzt hat.ich wusste nie, wie er grad draufist,musste immer vorsichtig sein. eine gefeuert zu bekommen, war eine erleichterung, denn daswar etwas was ich einschätzen konnte. ich hatte das emotional gut weg gepackt, konnte immergut drüber reden, es traf mich emotional überhaupt nicht. vor 4 jahren bedrohte mich die neuefrau meines ex mannes ( nicht der mann, der für das ganze vor 25 jahren verantwortlich ist)mich verbal und mit erhobener faust im beisein meiner kinder. sie kann mich nicht leiden undsah mich immer als konkurrenz. ab da gib es bergab und ein jahr später verbrachte ich 8
wochen in der psychiatrie. es hat jetzt nochmal 2 jahre gedauert und der kreis schließt sich.die emotionen kommen zum erlebten hinzu und das haut mich etwas von den socken, ich habeprobleme damit umzugehen. jahrelang habe ich geübt, erst nur das gefühl zu unterdrücken,dann kam die scham, die unterdrückte ich auch, weil sie nicht auszuhalten war. dann brauchtemein sohn mich, er ist ein "besonderes" kind und braucht bis heute besonderezuwendung. alsohabe ich meins gut weg gepackt... anderes war erstmal wichtiger. ich trank viel alkohol, machtewahnsinnig viel sport, verletzte mich selbst. bis derzusammenbruch kam. seit 14 tagen mussich üben...üben einen weg zu finden, erlerntes verhalten in teilen wieder abzulegen, weil es zurheilung nicht beiträgt es so zu lassen, wie es all die jahre üblich war. im moment ist es
schwierig aber das problem zu erkennen bedeutet auch, dass man anpacken kann... es ist nicht mehr unsichtbar 🙂

"do you have a drinking problem? " and "he said/she said" adding to  my finalized serise.

rant over.

text:
i know that most of you are aware of what happened to me 12 years ago and the aftermath of those events (my fibromyalgia and other health issues). it was recently in the press about a girls underwear being held up in court as “evidence “ for the defence which is exactly what happened to me.  this needs to stop, the reason people are afraid to go forward and report assault and abuse is that there remains a huge taboo around it and a culture of victim blaming. 
myself and sister queen @jillxfx have joined forces to raise awareness about rape, abuse and the prejudices surrounding it.  we would love it if our pageant family could take part.  if you would like to then take a photo in black and white with your mascara smudged either holding a white piece of paper or write “.... is not consent” on yourself.  you may chose the first part “ie marriage is not consent”, “dating is not consent” etc etc.  please tag both myself and jill in the post along with the hashtags 
#thisisnotconsent #crownsforacause #sisterqueensagainstsilence 
anyone can join in, male or female as this isn’t just something that affects women. 
i also have the following video i made 9 years ago if you would like to take a look: 
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iyojyetalia  #msnaturalbeautyscotland #thisisnotconsent #rapeawareness #crownsforacause #sisterqueensagainstsilence #metoo #rapesurvivor #standup #pageantqueen #pageant #beautyqueen #sisterqueens #awareness #campaign #antirape #fibromyalgia #spoonie #warrior #fibrowarrior

text:
“it’s christmas party time!” is this exclamation of merriment met with festive cheer – “yay, i wonder who my secret santa is” – or festive sneer – *groans, bangs head on desk, hides in toilet*? organising the christmas do can be a thankless task, but we salute you and are here to help.
‘tis the season to be jolly
…but should the suggestion of the christmas party be met with the same feeling and enthusiasm?
the inaugural festive do can be a daunting prospect for some employees, so should the expectation for everyone to attend exist? yes, the christmas party is your way of saying thank you, but your people have already dedicated 235 days, 1725 hours of their life to you this year, you can empathise that some may wish to pass on the bash. and indeed, for some employees with caring duties it may be an impossibility.
an invitation to the christmas party is key here – an invitation, rather than an expectation. for the most part, people will joyfully accept. but for those who don’t, they’ll appreciate your understanding and not being labelled a scrooge!
want to read more? check out our full blog on this, link in bio...
#christmas #christmasparty #officeparty #metoo #hr #humanresources #womeninbusiness #party #work #scrooge #barhumbug

text:
many people on here know that in feb. of this year i was physically assaulted by someone i loved and trusted, who was twice my size. what many people don’t know is—in the process of doing what i thought and still believe was right (leaving his ass and reporting him), i became a wanted person in the eyes of nypd. this isn’t about airing dirty laundry. this is about having a voice.
.
earlier this year, in april, i was arrested as a result of retaliation by my assaulter. recently, i got my release papers framed as an overall “fuck you” to the system and a reminder to myself of how much i’ve grown and learned (and continue to!) since the assault and arrest, thanks to an amazing support system (love y’all).
.
.
there aren’t many things more frightening than the cops calling you threatening felony charges, threatening to issue an arrest and search warrant, overstepping your constitutional rights, and demanding that you go “see” them. all while still having bruises on my arms and ribs (other body parts had since healed).
.
.
from first hand experience, i can tell you that we as a society still have a long way to go in terms of how we treat victims of all kinds who come forward. also bear with me as i have a pop culture moment and take this time to say fuck da police - the traumas you gave me have only made me stronger.
.
.
thank you for coming to my ted talk i am here to answer any questions and sadly no i do not have a copy of my mugshot <3
.
#metoo #believesurvivors #fuckthepolice

text:
a 17 year old rape victim lost her case in court, after a lawyer used her lace underwear to argue that she consented to sex. 
a similar case took place in 2002, where lindsay armstrong committed suicide, after the court made her hold up her underwear three times, which had “little devil” written across it, arguing that the style of the underwear proved consensual sex.

the sad part about rape, is that the victims feel more shame than the offender. 
linda armstrong, lindsay’s mother, stated “she felt she had been raped all over again during a trial that had left her humiliated and degraded.” underwear choice is not consent. 
clothing choice is not consent. 
1/5 women’s and 1/71 men, will be raped at some point in their lives. 
51.1 % of female victims of rape reported being raped by an intimate partner and 40.8 % by an acquaintance.
in 8/10 cases of rape, the victim knew the perpetrator. 
r.i.p angel👼 💕
#thisisnotconsent #metoo #metoomovement #rapevictim #rape #illustration #poem #poety #art

text:
selfcare comes in many shapes. sometimes, it's taking a bath; it can be having some alone time, reading a book, watching a film or it can be buying flowers for yourself. i do take a lot of selfcare lately - if you don't take good care of yourself, who else does?
this time, i'm going on holidays in the netherlands and i'm going to do something really crazy there. probably the craziest thing i've done in years. after all the struggles of the last years, i want to feel comfortable and empowered in my body. i don't want it to be only a shell, but a home again - and that needs a peace contract, a reminder for myself which i can turn to whenever i need it. that's why i finally fulfilled myself a pretty private wish and booked a lingerie shooting with @josefienhoekstra. i really admire her work and am really looking forward to the shoot and the results. (because lingerie is not consent, neither meant for male gaze - it's meant to empower women.) i combine this adventure with some days in amsterdam; spending some days abroad is truly freeing. are there places you can recommend? i want to see the most beautiful places and create a wonderful impression of this whole trip. :)

text:
the 9th oil that comes in your kit is frankincense! frank is my boyfriend! shh don’t tell my hubby! 😜 no but seriously, it’s so good for all the feels and glowing skin! there’s a reason that it was valued more than gold in ancient times and given to baby jesus! 
frankincense is very grounding and uplifting. diffuse it to create a calming atmosphere and feelings of spiritual connection. great for meditation or quiet time to relax.
my favorite way to use frank for my skin is with lavender and copaiba in jojoba oil in my glow serum. my skin has improved so much since i have started using this combo everyday! you can also use frank neat (without carrier oil) to reduce the appearance of fine lines, wrinkles and blemishes! 
i could go on and on about frankincense! 🤣

text:
do i feel like a crazy person with my constant talking about and pushing #ragebecomesher? 100%. am i one? no. am i angry? yes. am i using that anger? absolutely! this is the most important book i’ve read all year. it’s likely the most important one released all year. i bought this second copy (and the audible lol) so i can commit sacrilege and mark it up, highlight, take notes, etc. i’ve never ever done this to a book before so i think that speaks volumes about how vital it is. 
i'm verbose so as robin morgan put it: "to those who think #metoo has gone too far: read this book. to those who think #metoo hasn't gone far enough: read this book! to those who haven't given #metoo a thought: you damned well better read this book! soraya chemaly marshals solid research with unapologetic passion and humor, in compelling prose. men should read this book to understand women; women should read this book to understand themselves. rage becomes her could save your life." #sorayachemaly #bestbookof2018 #bookrecommendation #bookreview #importantreads #importantbooks #highlyrecommended #nonfiction #nonfictionnovember #bibliophile #bookstagram #book #bookshelf #bookclub #bookstagrammer #bookish #bookworm #booksofinstagram #booknerd #bookaholic #bookstagrammer #bookish #bookaddict #booklover #bookaddict #mustread

text:
- self harming isn’t attention seeking
- it isn’t done by just teenagers
- it doesn’t mean the person is suicidal
- self harm isn’t just cutting
- it isn’t done by one type of person

these are all stereotypes we need to break. stop stereotyping, stop making people feel guilty.
self harm is something we shouldn’t be ashamed of, it’s a symptom of a mental health condition it’s usually a way of coping with or expressing overwhelming emotional distress.

after years and years of being embarrassed and ashamed i am now proud of my scars, i no longer self harm but i see my scars as battle scars, yeah i might have had a few challenges in my life, some i didn’t think i would live through but i’m here, i’m standing strong and no way am i ashamed of that.
these scars are a reminder of how strong i am and the battles i have won.

lets end the stigma!!

text:
i’m asked every day “how do i become a hacker” . i tell people that the only way to learn to break shit is to actually get in and break it.

there’s no secret book or course that will give you hacker instincts. there are a lot of hackers out there. some are versatile enough to be useful on a project, most are not.  as for the most dangerous in this realm? without a doubt, steer clear of the social engineer with technical acumen and a vendetta.

why? because with only your last name and a general idea of where you have been in the last 30 days, i can wreak havoc so potent and so severe and from so many directions you have no chance of ever rebounding once i sink my talons into you.

start with osint, then move to script kiddie exploits, then experiment with customizing exploits that are surgically targeted. social engineering helps you zero in on and manipulate the target, technical prowess helps customize the exploits. 
who will hire you? check out law firms, security firms and contract firms that work with federal agencies.

there’s no secret book or course that will give you hacker instincts. there are a lot of hackers out there. some are versatile enough to be useful on a project, most are not.  as for the most dangerous in this realm? without a doubt, steer clear of the social engineer with technical acumen and a vendetta.

why? because with only your last name and a general idea of where you have been in the last 30 days, i can wreak havoc so potent and so severe and from so many directions you have no chance of ever rebounding once i sink my talons into you.

sta with osint, then move to script kiddie exploits, then experiment with customizing exploits that are surgically targeted. social engineering helps you zero in on and manipulate the target, technical prowess helps customize the exploits. 
who will hire you? check out law firms, security firms and contract firms that work with federal agencies.

text:
in un mondo perfetto, tutti gli uomini dell'ambiente musicale, dell'ambiente editoriale, ma anche tutti gli uomini d'italia, oggi dovrebbero prendere una posizione e dire "con persone di questo tipo io non lavorerò mai". non frega un cazzo a nessuno, quanto individui che violentano, molestano, picchiano siano bravi in quello che fanno.
non dovrebbe fregare un cazzo a nessuno quanti bei festival organizzino, quanti bravi artisti facciano suonare. questi esseri dovrebbero essere licenziati, cacciati, condannati.
non ci sono scelte, ci sono doveri.
e il dovere di tutt* è quello di smettere di supportare le merde che circolano, smettere di guardare film di woody allen, di muccino, di andare ai concerti organizzati da emanuele podestà, se ne organizzerà ancora.
e nel farlo, sempre, e dico sempre, rispettare le vittime, la loro richiesta di silenzio e la loro privacy, e supportarle con ogni mezzo.

e già che ci siete educate i vostri cazzo di figli come esseri umani quantomeno decenti.

text: one of the really cool things about studying in strasbourg is that european institutions often become your classroom. this week, my class on international communication in european media is attending the 2018 world forum for democracy at the council of europe. this year’s theme is “gender equality: whose battle,” with international leaders and activists discussing how to combat gender inequality around the world through legislation, education, and other tangible actions. our class separated into groups to produce news packages on various issues presented throughout the forum. my group is working on a video on the influence of the #metoo movement in bringing more attention to the prevalence of gender-based violence around the world. #gwfofac #gwabroad #strasbourg

text:
insomma, anche oggi nella civile italia è stata una giornata da dimenticare, specialmente per le donne. questa mattina l'eures ha diramato l'aggiornamento dei dati sul femminicidio: nei primi dieci mesi del 2018, sono state 106 le vittime di femminicidio in italia (pensate se 106 donne fossero state uccise da degli immigrati). nel pomeriggio, #silviaromano, una cooperante di 23 anni,milanese, che si trovava in kenya con una onlus per dare assistenza ai bambini è stata rapita da un commando di fondamentalisti islamici. e su internet dei decerebrati senza palle né dignità hanno scritto oscenità come: "se ne è andata non di certo gratis! se voleva fare volontariato, poteva farlo benissimo in italia, ora ha creato solo problemi”, oppure “ennesima oca giuliva, poteva stare a casa e aiutare gli italiani”. infine, la giornata sta volgendo al termine con lo scandalo di #losapevanotutti con cui, a partire dalla denuncia di #federicofiumani, il mondo della musica sta accusando il manager della casa editrice #habanero, nonché organizzatore di un festival molto famoso a #genova e dintorni, di aver usato violenza contro tantissime ragazze. a detta di molte emanuele habanero podestà le avrebbe ricattate, chiedendo sesso in cambio della pubblicazione dei loro manoscritti e avrebbe picchiato, segregato e minacciato di morte molte altre. senza che nessuno proferisse parola. essere donna in italia è ancora una misera sfida. (in 📷 un lavoro di quei geni di @cheapfestival )

text:
here is a "positives" update:
- i am so thankful for all of the love and support i have been receiving through out my mental health recovery. - i absolutely love my job as a senior care manager. - wanda and i are moving out with roommates at the beginning of next week and i am super excited! - i am so grateful for my cat. she helps calm me when i need it. - i am super grateful for my sisters, brother in law, my boyfriend, my aunt (@travelqueen007 ), my nieces, and my closest friends. i wouldn't have been able to make it this far in life without them and i appreciate and love them more than i can put into words. 
i hope everyone is having a wonderful day!💗

text:
this week’s wic wednesday is christine wilson, our shelter manager at marianne’s place!

how did you get involved with wic? 
i started volunteering with wic, got to know the agency and within the year i got hired on as relief staff for the shelter. i went from relief to team lead and after about 10 years of that i went into the volunteer coordinator role. i took a year off because i had my daughter then i came back for a two years and continued as the volunteer manager until the current shelter manager left. after that i put my name in the hat for the residential manager and have been here every since, which has been about 12 years.
.
.
what changes have you seen during your time with wic?
the world has changed and by reflection we’ve seen how the work has changed. how information is so at your fingertips now, the pervasive needs that people have around supports. everybody is dealing with so many different barriers because system navigation has been even more difficult and more of a struggle. even things like the #metoo movement, conversations are happening now that we’ve known for a while. it’s a bit validating that we aren’t alone in this fight anymore. .
.
what do you do outside of work?
raise a couple kids, one is a teenager. but what i do for fun is i usually play some sort of sport. i play ball hockey in the winter and spring and then softball in the summer. my partner and i do renovations on our own house so we usually have an ongoing project. in the summer, we go camping, that’s a huge part. i try and do stuff in the winter like skating, skiing with the kids.
.
.
what would you say to someone about to donate to wic?
they’re helping woman and their kids leave violence and have a chance and a safer start. sometimes the donation doesn’t always have to be big, it doesn’t have to be money, sometimes those in-kind donations can go a long way. it’s about feeling like you’re a part of the solution. when you’re volunteering or donating places, it’s your chance to make a positive in this world.

join us on november 22 at the assembly hall lawns for our clothes line project as we recognize the international day for the elimination of violence against women

i haven’t always done the best i could but i’m working towards that.
.
i buried it for years. i let it eat a part of me away. i didn’t speak up.
.
i only started taking medication that i’ve probably needed for most of my life a few months ago and it’s like i’d been living my life as a clenched fist and the grip is finally starting to loosen.
.
i could say that i don’t regret it because regret is useless but i do and i’ve been beating myself up about not starting meds sooner. i know i don’t have to feel shame but those feelings of regret are part of the process whether or not they’re feelings i should or shouldn’t have.
.
i am still learning to carry this. i am still a work in progress. i’ll never stop being a work in progress because there is no tangible finish line to healing.
.
i’m not a good example of someone who came out the other side stronger. but i am strong. anyone who is a survivor of trauma, sexual or otherwise, is strong for surviving but it’s not the source of our strength.
.
i was always strong but strength doesn’t always help you get through. it’s not always enough. and that’s ok.
.
asking for help and accepting it don’t diminish your strength, they help you reinforce the strength you already have. healing is messy. recovery isn’t perfect. and you don’t have to do it alone.
.
you are enough. mess and all.
.

text:
got mah hurr did. #thankful 
not many people think about haircuts. i mean... why should you? you walk in and get it done, right? 
no. not everyone. 
some of us pass salons, think about calling 273,948-times... and then don’t. if we can’t get to “our shop” or “our #stylist,” we’ll let our hair grow out like shabby shaggy manes rather than risk someone else touching us. it’s not that “our shop” or “our stylist” is the only capable place or person on earth, but... kind of. 
for the #survivor of physical #abuse, of #rape, of #sexualassault, the #trust we hold for people we touch and let touch us (including family and friends) is enormous! 
for something as seemingly simple as a haircut? our neck’s bent backward over a shampoo bowl, and—in those moments—our vision might be compromised by bright ceiling lights. our head’s in someone else’s hands, and our body’s prone. this position might feel good or be relaxing for some, but for a survivor it can foster anxiety and fear. it can cause flashbacks. it’s not abnormal to panic in this position. so, #faith in “our person” is kind of a big deal. *my person* is almost 9-years #safe for me. she understands my backstory and accepts my repercussion quirks. she’s #compassionate and #sympathetic. she’s #funny. she’s #kind. she’s #patient. she’s a boss stylist and a terrific human. i depend on her. she’s important to me. 
what you take for granted might be another’s struggle. maybe think of this when you’re frustrated or impatient with someone who’s hesitant or slow, flustered, or jumpy... seemingly “without reason.” we all make it to “the finish line” after varying degrees of pain and suffering in this life. we all end with varying degrees of damage. you won’t get everyone’s backstory, won’t have the slightest clue from where some people come. but, if you really mean #loveoneanother #weareone #believewomen #metoo #mentalhealthmatters or any other movement, maybe try... try to practice more than armchair activism and truly, truly exercise #empathy. 
#growth #strength #peace #confidence #courageovercomfort #beyourself #beyourownkindofbeautiful 
non-#bicycle non-#cycling #cyclist post

text:
according to #tmz-“the #hollywood chamber of commerce tells us the stars will be fixed today, and they believe the perp(s) will be caught, because the walk is lined with security cameras.

#jenniferlopez now has a strange and unlikely connection to #donald trump and #billcosby ... because her star on the hollywood walk of fame caught the attention of a vandal. 
someone used what looks like black spray paint to deface j lo's star tuesday ... near the famed intersection of hollywood and vine. it's not clear what message, if any, the tagger was trying to send.
cops took a vandalism report and will investigate the incident. the paint job's bad, but not nearly as destructive as what we've seen on the walk of fame earlier this year.

most of the vandalism has been focused on trump's star ... with george lopez unleashing a massive fake pee stream over it, plus the golden toilet incident, the infamous pickax attack and this sticky situation. it's gotten so bad, there was talk about removing the star permanently while potus is in office.
as for cosby -- after he was sentenced to 3 to 10 years in prison for sexual assault, someone scribbled the words "serial rapist." and "#metoo" on his star. fellow stars #pharellwilliams #ellendegeneres and #michaelbubble’s hollywood stars were also hit by this act of vandalism. it appears the coc was quick on the cleanup effort. at least as far as buble is concerned, the all stars have been scrubbed clean already.”👀😮 (via @tmz_tv) #rap #hiphop #rnb #latin #pop #aka #love #onthe6 #rebirth #jlo #onthefloor #followus #followbackalways  #followforfollow #follow4follow #gainpost

text: my favourite breakfast at the moment. fresh fruit (strawberries & rockmelon), greek yoghurt & chia seeds. since my ptsd reared it’s ugly head again, i’ve been yoyo dieting. skipping meals, eating too much, binging, starving..... basically doing everything wrong. since feeling more like me, my ptsd managed somewhat, i’ve made a huge effort with my nutrition. i know what works for me. i’ve just ignored it these past near two years. no more. back to basics. the weight won’t come off over night (if only 🤷🏼‍♀️), it didn’t go on over night. i didn’t even weigh myself at the beginning of when my change started, yet since i did weigh myself (last thursday), this morning i re-weighed myself & i had lost 1.3kg’s. no tricks. no pills. no shakes. no skipping meals. no giving up the treats completely. not even much exercise. just proper eating. feeling so much better. mindset is so good. i don’t feel like it’s a chore. it’s not a forced effort. it is, just is. #metoo #believesurvivors #selfdevelopment #selfdiscovery #taekwondo #fitness #health #weightloss #healing #mypeakchallenge #journey #betterinsideandout #makingchanges

text:
the year is about to finish and i wanted to highlight some of my favourite books. "until i'm yours" by @kennedyryan1 is one of them.

it's an amazing romance and at the same time the author talks about sexual abuse and how often the victims are judged instead of the abuser. it's a harsh reality, to be a woman in such a misogynist society but the romance genre it's a safe environment for us and even if sofie has been abused she gets the happy ending that she deserves. and she falls in love with trevor, a man who respects her, cares for her and supports her. 💚
💚

have you read this book? do you think that the romance genre is a safe place for women? •
•

text:
another snippet from the rehearsal process of «reset», the piece i got to develop on and with the current students at @trondertundans 🖤
. . .
with abortion becomming criminalised in ohio, an irish 17-year old girl having her underwear used as evidence that she was to blame for getting raped and people like trump and kavanaugh  holding positions of power despite heavy evidence against them that they have both mistreated and abused women around them, i felt it was high time to lend my creative voice to the #metoo movement. this is the time to speak up and rally together (no matter what gender) against the people who wants to surpress our rights and dehumanize us. when i hear this song in particular, i don’t just hear «what kind of man», but «what kind of human». it is time to reset and reform the preconceptions of society. 
#whatkindofman @florenceandthemachine #contemporary #choreography

text:
all i wanted to do that day was immortalize my youth my beauty! #metoo #timesup #timesupnow
earlier this week i found myself sobbing uncontrollably! it hit me like a freight train as i thought back over the course of my life the times i had been sexually harassed, sexually abused, and sexually assaulted most by men i knew some of whom i attended edinboro and cheyney with. people often ask why i don't have any solid professional photos and the truth is after september 2009 when i invited a photographer friend who i had known at that point for 15 years into my home  to shoot me and it turn into a sexual harassment photo session  i have  not been able to  bring myself to sit for a photographer in studio! i would make appointments with some of the best and well respected photographers in ny and cancel at the last second! i remember telling one of my college besties about what had transpired in my home the day of the shoot and she blamed me for presenting myself to him in a sexy and provocative way. "what did you expect to happen?" she said. "i mean you're walking around half naked!" my head was fucked up! but i what i have not dealt with is the trauma. the trauma of trying to reconcile whether or not i was responsible for how a man behaves towards me...... this is too much! i am drained! so basically i cannot be in a photo session alone because the photographer is going to try and fuck me. ... and whenever i hear a photographer say to me "i gotta get you in the studio" my skin crawls, my mouth drys out, my chest tightens and all i can say to myself is no motherfucker you will not get me in your studio your chambers of hell.. no you will not (to be continued)

text: 📚 conceição evaristo // nascida em 1946 e criada na favela do pindura saia, mesmo ao lado de uma zona nobre de belo horizonte (mg), ela trabalhou como empregada doméstica até concluir o curso normal, para tornar-se professora primária. mudou-se para o rio de janeiro, e fez parte do grupo quilombhoje, em cuja série literária, cadernos negros, publicou seus primeiros poemas. graduou-se mestra em literatura brasileira pela puc-rio e doutora em literatura comparada pela universidade federal fluminense, e é hoje professora visitante na ufmg. seus dois primeiros romances, 'ponciá vicêncio' (2003) e 'becos da memória' (2006), foram reeditados no ano passado. para ler hoje.

text: i was delighted but a little confused at first about why the geniuses behind the @nytimes truth ad campaign wanted to feature our 8 spectacular pies project — they usually highlight the harder news coverage, trump and #metoo. but: they're geniuses. they wanted to highlight the diligence, the attention to detail, the sheer amount of work that goes into everything the times does — even pies. and there were dozens of ideas from @emcdowell, our writer, countless emails and phone calls and several days on set. each of our final pies was made several times over, and that doesn't even count the reject pies — which means that well over a hundred pies were baked in order to bring you something delicious and ingenious. then there were recipes to edit, photos to shoot, videos to produce. a lot of obscenely talented people worked on this project and i'm so proud it was chosen to be featured. and you can hear me saying "over and over" about halfway through if you listen closely enough. long live the truth, especially at 400 degrees for 40 minutes! @nytcooking #nytpies nytimes.com/pie

text:
last week, i had the honor of representing the @equalityleague's advisory council at their first reception (hence the flower in my fro) and i got to meet a whole bunch of inspiring women. the conversation of the night was about how eql is going to be one of the leading organizations in global human rights and sports.⠀
⠀
two women who i talked to that night really stand out to me in these pictures.⠀
⠀
first, nancy hogshead-makar: olympic gold medalist in swimming and sports human rights lawyer. i interviewed her at the players' tribune and it's always amazing being around her light (and her superb photo editing skills lol). she's helped to defend many athletes in the #metoo era and helped to pass the safe sport act.⠀
⠀
second, judge rosemarie aquilina (in the center): the judge who sentenced larry nassar in the usa gymnastics sex abuse scandal.⠀
⠀
i'm so grateful that i get to be surrounded by such incredible and highly influential women and men.⠀
⠀

text:
so i was looking to post a picture for the school, and all the skaters we had were male, and we do have a bunch of females who skate. so i started searching social media for images of females shredding. 
all but the one on the top left were simply ads of girls selling clothes holding longboards. i used it. she was strong. 
but was it the most popular because she wore a bikini top? it started a whole conversation with myself, in my head, about what objectification means in conjunction with social media in the #metoo era. 
is it victim blaming, if you shudder when you see your daughter or her friends posting pictures of themselves in bikinis? i think so. 
yet you do worry for their safety. do you worry for their reputation? for the way men they meet might prejudge them? or future employers? can they be taken seriously as intellectuals? 
you do have some of these thoughts with your son, but never about his appearance. how is this fair? how is this right? how can we move past it without discussing it? at least we are, right? #thekidsarealright

text:
editor’s note:
the reason i wanted to put together this photo shoot for our body episode is because the me too movement holds a special place in my heart. women rule my life, from my mother and my sisters, my nieces and from aunts to my grandmothers, my friends and my co-workers i am surrounded by strong beautiful women. i see women as precious intelligent creators that should be held at the highest esteem. i understand and acknowledge that i am a white male and in america, being a white male, it is my responsibility to use the privilege that was forced upon me at birth for something greater. it is not enough to live in my privilege, but if i am able to take it and bestow it upon others in their time of need then i feel like i am worth more than what is seen skin deep. no one deserves to be abused in any way, especially sexually. there is not a single thing any woman or man can do to warrant sexual abuse. i have suffered my own unwarranted sexual advances and i have dealt with and have seen so much sexual abuse in my short lifetime that i need the world, everyone of all ages, races, sexuality, and gender who have been sexually abused in any way, to know that zynon stands with you, that i stand with you. you are not alone. #metoo ~ @kalobdaniel
photography by @aminaeffinshaw and @sabrinadunnephoto

text:
is the la district attorneys office protecting a man for his politics?
_____________________________________
michael avenatti (dubbed "creepy porn lawyer") escaped prosecution of the felony charges lobbied against him by a number of women he has allegedly assaulted. most recent among these women is his recently estranged wife, lisa. with multiple bruises and scrapes, it is uncountable that the woman was physically attacked. michael even admitted to the crime in his own defense statement "she hit me first". of course, i am not one to 'believe all women' but this is a case where the evidence is clear. the district attorneys attempts to downplay the scenario as a misdemeanor are indeed egregious and i would never stand by them.
_____________________________________
with evidence and this not being the first instance not withstanding, michael avenatti should be charged with a felony. the fact that the district attorneys refuse to charge him with such could really only mean one thing, they are protecting him for his role in the anti-trump movement. regardless of feeling about trump, chivalry is not dead yet. beating women is gross. it's one thing of she used lethal force or attacked you in a way that required self defense, it's an entirely other issue if you have a history of abuse and you came away without a mark.
#avenatti #trump #conservative #walkaway #freespeech #politics #political #publicsquare #metoo

text:
"kou aeap rhat mou aow" - 9x12" - oil on canvas board
.
i was going to sleep one night when out of nowhere, i had three visions within like 5 minutes. this was one of them (the other two - soon to follow). took notes...the next morning, i did extensive research on every angle of this piece to cover my ass. .
...i succeeded.
.
we've all heard that even the prison system has etiquette - they hate #rapists. and we must never forget that rape is the only crime that can never be attributed to survival. eventually the suspect becomes the victim within prison walls. karma has a face too. you reap what you sow.
.
kou aeap rhat mou aow
.
as i've mentioned before, when you paint a portrait, you really get pulled into it - hours at a time. in this case it was hell. #harveyweinstein has one of the ugliest faces i've ever seen. his eyes gave me anxiety attacks. the crevices in his skin were horrid. his lack of eyebrows creepy. but being in your comfort zone will kill you anyways.
.
.
.

text:
this i not what i normally post here, but i felt something needed to be said; rape is not about sex or love it's about power. power that's left in the hands of the accused, and this time like many others, the accuser has won. this girl was victimized in her own court hearing, "you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front" (the exact words of the judge) she was forced to hold her own underwear up for everyone to see. the case was dismissed and the accused was acquitted. now the 27 year old man will continue to walk free and the 17 year old girl who just wanted to get justice for herself, is dead. there's nothing that can be done to bring her back, no amount of social media posts or hashtags or rallies can bring her back, but it can keep her story alive. girls, boys, women and men are ashamed to go to the authorities when they experience rape or sexual assault, so many cases are dismissed and the victims are humiliated, left with nothing but their story. this is not fair. if they're not taken seriously no one will come forth and thousands of accusers will continue to walk the streets with nothing but pride and not a single punishment. don't be afraid to get help, call 911, go to the police, protect yourself so you can protect those who might have come after you.
#metoo #thisisnotconsent

text:
before i wake - watercolor - 10 x 14 inches

the title of the painting comes from a child’s bedtime prayer: “now i lay me down to sleep.
i pray the lord my soul to keep.
if i should die before i wake,
i pray to god my soul to take.” this watercolor sketch was one of the first of many attempts to paint how things change. in this sketch there is the change from interior to exterior— from the confines of the room out onto the spaces of the road and into the landscape and mountains in the distance. the little girl runs between one reality into another.

years later i’m still trying to paint metaphors for change.
years later, the little girl tells me she is still running.

#metoo #fineart #contemporaryart #realistart #nightvisions #visualpoetry #landscapes #visionaryart #visualpoetry #surrealistart

text: tomorrow's a funny day, the day to follow is hysterical. it's like let's be grateful for 3 hours, then violently purge consumerism the next day. i just need to say, i'm enough, good, bad, any random misplaced judgements; whatever i'm enough. can't show up to celebrations as myself, actually dressed not in pajamas semi decently in a sweater to be sent to change because my sweater is ugly. i showed up right? i hope whatever home stuff people are going through is either avoided or put down for the day. america was stolen, although togetherness days are important. it's just funny to me, how tomorrow is gratitude day. yet it seems any other day is the day to provoke losses on each other. life's not really a competition, i like what i have, and nothing else is needed. furthering advancement and accomplishments that aren't blood soaked from others means something to me. i hope tomorrow lasts, and not in ways of celebrating genocide, that's terrible. in ways of i hope we all start thankfullyliving everyday. stop roadblocking education and progress. definetly stop trying to slaughter the kids and anyone who sees enough good in you to care for a moment. real sick of being treated like kenny from south park. if someone sees the good in you, notice that's part of how they love themselves, refrain from attacking them for it, they will no longer see the good in you. see the good in the future of those child hostages. respectfully, humanely. have a happy day, however you do. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors p.s. i love my doggie friend companion homey!

text:
tejiendo el movimiento. weaving @theglobaldressmovement ♥️ soy paz ♥️ soy amor ♥️ soy poder ♥️ soy mujer ♥️
♥️i am peace ♥️ i am love ♥️ i am power ♥️i am a woman ♥️
la violencia de género e inequidad son de los problemas más álgidos y más visibles en estos tiempos de la humanidad. en el 2016, se lleva a cabo en perú y en muchos lugares del mundo, la marcha ni una menos que denuncia la desaparición de mujeres debido a la violencia. la diseñadora carola solis (perú) crea el vestido #soypazsoyamorsoypodersoymujer para participar desde la sanacion. en 2017, la pedagoga, maestra de yoga christine mcardle oquendo (estados unidos) ve el vestido en una formación de yoga para niños a la que carola asiste, y tiene la visión de crear una comunidad que una, promueva la educación y sanación, teniendo el vestido como punto de partida, complementando con muchas otras herramientas que les iremos compartiendo. este sábado 24 marcharemos! unete al movimiento!
♥️⭕️♥️
gender violence and inequality are the most critical and visible problems at these times of humanity. in 2016, the march "ni una menos" denounced the disappearance of women due to violence in peru and in many parts of the world. the #designer carola solis creates the dress #soypazsoyamorsoypodersoymujer to participate of the march from a healing perspective.in 2017, the pedagogue, yoga teacher christine mcardle sees the dress in a yoga training for children that carola attends, and has the vision of creating a community that unites, promotes education and healing in this subject, taking the dress as a starting point, complementing with many other tools, which we will share soon. and this november 24th we march at the 25n ni una menos march. join the movement!

text:
i just want to take a moment to express my sincere gratitude for each and every one of you who has been a part of my journey and the evolution of cara blanchard training, inc. over the past year. i had to make some difficult decisions in changing my business in order to do what was best, and healthiest, for my horses and myself. these decisions have also allowed me to begin pursuing one of my ultimate lifelong goals of competing at the international level by purchasing fiona. the moment i saw her i knew an incredible adventure was about to happen - she’s a dream come true! this summer when i told part of steele’s story (http://carablanchardtraining.com/shame-on-you/) and received an incredible amount of support, cbt began to take the shape that i had always hoped it would. while promoting and sharing my passion for classical dressage, i am also able to speak about equine welfare and doing right by every horse. i have even shared stories about some of the abuse i’ve personally endured and hopefully been able to inspire others to believe in themselves. thank you for allowing me to be a part in your journeys, i’m truly humbled. please don’t ever give up and always enjoy the ride! what a wonderful thought it is that some of our best days haven’t even happened yet! 💝

text:
#feminicidio #arequipa

noviembre representa, para nosotras, la lucha por nuestros derechos y por la supervivencia ante personas que aún no comprenden que no somos de su propiedad.

sin embargo en esta lucha, katherine monroy huanca de 18 años, perdió la batalla y fue asesinada por el que fuera su pareja renzo condori sucari de 18 años en el distrito de miraflores.

el cuerpo calcinado de katherine fue encontrado recostado en su cama, haciendo con ello que los peritos dudarán de que esa fuera la razón de su muerte. gracias a las investigaciones y los vecinos que señalaron que su ex pareja la acosaba y que estuvo horas antes en la puerta de su casa, es que las investigaciones apuntaron a un sospechoso, quien horas después confeso que efectivamente él la había asesinado.

hoy nuevamente nos sentimos de manos atadas, porque si bien somos más las organizaciones que luchamos contra este tipo de hechos, aún no hemos podido lograr sensibilizar y concientizar a aquellas personas que siguen pensando que nuestras vidas les pertenecen.

desde nuestra plataforma, nuestra solidaridad con la familia y con todos aquellos que conocieron a katherine monroy, una vida que tenía mucho por conocer y aprender, pero que sin embargo hoy se ve apagada por el machismo y la crueldad de un sujeto que la prefirió muerta antes que perdida.

you can't help but laugh moment😂: i  was picking tara up from school today and she had been busy working on her whales and sharks for her under the sea diorama. as we were walking out i asked her if she wanted to make an octupus for her diorama when we get home. her response was, and at the top of her lungs may i add, "muuuuum it's not runny poos!!!" i was like no that's what it's called a diorama, runny poos is called diarrhoea 😂😂😂😂😂😂

_____________
🌕the full moon brought an aha moment. i had unfinished business and work to do to use this new found voice of mine to create boundaries, say no more and forgive.
______________
🙏i will never forget. but i forgive the people who created chaos and havoc with malicious intentions. there is much healing to do but i am taking back my energy that has been leaking and the pieces of me they have held. 
________________
yoga means union and male-female relationships universally need healing. not just between people but within ourselves. 
______________ 🌊trauma recovery is an ongoing process. what takes some people down one path of reaction does not effect others in the same way. healing happens in a unique way as well. i created gamapyc because i was called to. in the process of holding space for others to heal... i find myself healing too. 😀
__________________
metta,
monica🙏

text:
kepolisian india telah mendaftarkan sebuah kasus ke pengadilan yang melibatkan aktor india, alok nath. alok nath dituntut atas tuduhan pemerkosaan oleh produsernya, vinta nanda. kasus alok nath hanyalah satu dari segelintir kasus yang benar-benar diterima oleh kepolisian sejak munculnya gerakan #metoomovement.

kasus pemerkosaan oleh alok nath sebelumnya dibeberkan oleh nanda melalui laman facebooknya pada bulan oktober lalu. nath sendiri membantah tuduhan tersebut dan melayangkan gugatan balasan kepada nanda. ia meminta nanda memohon maaf dan meminta kompensasi simbolis sebesar 1 rupee

tuduhan perkosaan kepada alok nath tidak hanya dilayangkan oleh nanda, dikabarkan ada dua aktris lainnya yang melayangkan tuduhan serupa.

nanda terlibat dalam suatu proyek bersama nath di tahun 1990, yakni kala mereka mengerjakan serial televisi berjudul tara. nanda mengaku butuh waktu untuk mengumpulkan keberanian selama 19 tahun untuk mengungkapkan apa yang dialaminya.

dalam tulisan di laman facebooknya, nanda tidak menyebut secara spesifik siapa aktor yang ia maksud. ia baru mengakui bahwa yang ia maksud adalah alok nath di kemudian hari.

di sisi lain, alok nath mengatakan bahwa ia percaya bahwa pemerkosaan telah terjadi, namun bukan ia pelakunya.

dalam beberapa bulan terakhir gerakan #metoomovement telah membesar, menumbuhkan keberanian bagi para wanita untuk mengungkapkan apa yang mereka alami. gerakan ini menyeret banyak nama, termasuk dari kalangan aktor, jurnalis, komedian, penulis, sutradara, hingga pejabat publik.

tanushree dutta adalah aktris pertama yang melaporkan pelecehan seksual yang ia alami 10 tahun lalu. pelecehan tersebut dilakukan oleh aktor yang menjadi lawan mainnya, nana patekar. sejak saat itu, para wanita memiliki keberanian untuk melaporkan pelecehan dan kekerasan seksual terhadap mereka
.
.source by : akurat .
.
follow : @dunia_india @dunia_india2 .
.
#aloknath #metoo  #vintananda #bollywood #duniaindia2

pronouncement of gratitude from my aistic self to you. thank you for following me. 
i’ve reached a tipping point where elements in my life are cooperating on the love kadie’s creativity side - of my psyche, which allows me to share more of myself with you. i have tended towards abandoning my most creative urges - because - life. but my understanding of my core power has shifted a lot. 
my life has changed a lot in the past year and a half and it’s given me an oppounity to know myself better. and see that i’m better (i feel so much better) when i allow myself to express my creativity, which often comes out in weird and surprising ways. i’m embracing that. not gonna judge it anymore. 
i’m thankful for female friends who do their aist thing in ways that move me more into mine, who i’ve known for years, who have sat with me, shared their perspectives, their paths, their struggles, their talent, and included me in awesome projects of theirs. 
 
ittlespiralmusic

ssencemusic

 
 
i thank myself for allowing myself to indulge my stories, my songs, my whimsical and surrealist dreams. outloud. in front of you. this is some scary s—-. but it’s juicing me up and i feel more alive and present with myself than ever.

text:
let's see what is this cause about.

in recent years delhi's uprising crime in terms of molestation, eve teasing, harassment, etc has been a constant issue while all the official authorities fail to make delhi safe.
 this cause is an ideology to make delhi safe again, to help protect and uplift the women's safety and security in delhi. we need to make this collective measures by volunteering as a team to act upon these things, most importantly get out of social media and do something about it for real. let's make this happen in a vision that every time a man tries to eve tease or do anything wrong, he shall think there's someone doing something about it. looking forward for all your support!

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
questo 25 novembre, si fa fatica a scrivere, perché le parole risuonano sempre più inutili, cadono vane nel vuoto lasciato dalle donne alle quali la vita è stata interrotta, all'improvviso, perché un uomo ha deciso che quella vita non potevano, non meritavano di continuare a viverla.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

#metoo: `how do we bring sensitivity to such people', revathy asks mohanlal

actor revathy has come out against mohanlal on his #metoo comment where he had said that it is a fashion for some people. she inquired how can they make these insensitive people understand the seriousness of abuse. she has responded on twitter without naming the superstar.

история о жёнах грабителей, погибших при неудачном налёте. новоиспечённые вдовы берутся сами закончить начатое, разобраться с полицией и конкурентами, а главное – выяснить, кто же подставил их мужей.
вам понравился «8 подруг оушена»? группа девушек совершает ограбление, наверное вы его сразу и вспомнили. есть некая схожесть, но во «вдовах» будет гораздо больше драмы, несправедливости и расовой дискриминации. история сильных женщин во главе с виолой дэвис - актуально в эпоху #metoo. и именно поэтому фильм, скорее всего, будет участвовать в наградном сезоне. обязательно посмотрите) #diepremiere

text:
when it comes to sexual harassment questions have been raised over the value of anonymous reporting, for example can action be taken when reports are anonymous? at what point is the identity of the complainant and the accused revealed?
sadly, distrust that complaints will be taken seriously or fear of raising your hand and reporting a grievance prevail. confidential reporting gives voice to the voiceless; after all, harassment is about power remember, so anonymity and self-preservation allows victims to regain some of that control they feel they may have lost.
at tell jane we provide a safe space for employees to report incidences and concerns of workplace harassment confidentially through a freephone hotline manned by experienced hr practitioners.  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
facing the future! from today’s book trade press:

two deals for alexandra heminsley
news - books thursday, 22 november 2018
non-fiction exploration of the body for chatto and two novels with sphere for grazia books editor and judy murray's ghost

becky hardie at chatto & windus and ed wood at sphere have separately acquired new works of non-fiction and fiction respectively by bestselling author, journalist and broadcaster alexandra heminsley. the deals were simultaneously brokered by sarah ballard at united agents. 
hardie has acquired at auction some body to love by heminsley, a memoir and ‘biography of her body’. according to a statement from ua: 'in the era of #metoo and the gra (gender recognition act), heminsley reconsiders her relationship with her own body as women everywhere do the same. she looks from adolescence to now as mother to the baby boy she is co-parenting with her former partner who is embarking on transition (mtf). how can we learn to best enjoy our bodies without being defined by them? how best to mother a son when what it is to be a woman is being renegotiated so publicly? chatto will publish in early 2021.' hardie said: "we are so happy to welcome alex to chatto for some body to love. she's made a career out of writing honestly and perceptively about her relationship with her body, but this new book promises a whole new level of questioning and understanding. she's such a trusted voice and i can't wait to hear what she has to say." meanwhile wood, editorial director at sphere, has acquired at auction two book club-style novels by heminsley – the first time she has written fiction under her own name. the first, as-yet-untitled debut novel, is an emotional story about two half-sisters that brings nature writing into the fiction arena. sphere will publish in 2021. 
wood said: "with her incisive non-fiction, alex showed how beautifully she could portray our emotional relationship with the natural world through physicality. this book will bring all that talent to an incredibly moving novel of grief, hope and empowerment that will speak to a universal readership. i couldn’t be more proud to be publishing her fiction."

text:
il y a des jours comme ça où je n'ai pas la patience. pas envie d'être "gentille". pas envie de me faire suivre par un mec dans la part dieu quand je cherche des idées de cadeaux pour mes proches. 
pas envie qu'un mec lambda me suive et me dise "hey jolie". par contre j'ai envie que qu'on me comprenne quand je dis non. 
envie qu'on ne me dise pas "pourquoi tu es méchante je t'ai pas insultée" en continuant à me suivre et en me disant que c'est moi la méchante parce que j'agresse. 
envie que les gens qui se sont arrêté pour regarder cet homme très près de moi sans mon consentement agissent au lieu de regarder la scène ébahis et choqués.

et surtout j'aimerai me sentir en sécurité quand je fais ma vie tranquille. et j'aimerai ne pas avoir envie de pleurer de frustration de colère et de peur.

merci bien.

text:
| 人人的metoo |

你聽過metoo嗎？

#metoo 起源發想
社運人士tarana burke於2006年發起一場草根運動，在被性侵犯的有色人種、底層女性中推廣「用同理心實現賦權（empowerment through empathy）」。那時有一位13歲的少女向她傾訴曾遭受的性侵犯經歷，而她當時不知該如何回應。這一經歷啟發她開始使用「metoo」一詞，她說她希望當時能用這個詞來回應那位少女，而之後「metoo」則成爲這場運動的一部分。

#metoo 影響發酵
2017年10月15日，女演員 alyssa milano 在推特上鼓勵女性儘可能地傳播這個詞，使人們能意識到該問題的嚴重性與普通性。
當時她寫到：「如果所有被性騷擾或侵犯過的女性都能發一條『metoo』的狀態，那人們或許能認識到這個問題的重要性」。
此之後，數百萬人使用了這一標籤來公開她們的不快經歷，其中也包括許多知名人士。
而一些男性則通過標籤「我會如何改變」（howiwillchange）來承認他們有過對女性的無禮行為。

text:
in case you missed it, here’s a sneak peek into the panel discussion post #foreignbodyplay! it was an intriguing conversation with imogen butler-cole, @priyankabose20 and our very own @dizibot on law, justice & survival.

what counts as justice from the point of view of the survivor? in the light of the latest discussion on the #metoo movement, what does speaking out years after the experience do to the survivor or mean for the survivor? what do we as a society, as individuals listening to the survivor stories, do? how do we ensure support and safe spaces for people to come forward and share their story?

these were only a few questions that were asked, and the answers could perhaps begin to be attempted. #bangalore #pondicherry #ahmedabad #jaipur -- if you want to catch a showing, you can still! more details: www.foreignbodyplay.com

#metooindia #foreignbody #imogenbutlercole #performance #showing #mumbai #mumbaievents #bombay #bombayevents #support #survivor #survival #violence #sexualviolence #vaw #endvaw #endvawg #endgbv

text:
"me too" 
seerat kaur

me too, to the fresh faced, frecky preteen.
me too, to the goth waif in black skinny jeans.
me too, to the mom with a bob in the van.
me too, to the raven haired surfer with a tan.
me too, to my classmate in the hip mini skirt.
me too, to my colleague in the checkered shirt.
me too, to my buddy with luxurious curls.
me too, to my daughter, my niece, my sister.
me too, to my mother, my aunt and you mister.
it's heartbreaking, its scary, but most definitely true.
its happened to her and it's part of me too.
we hid it to rid it..but deep down we all knew and now that it's surfaced.
what shall we do? 
it happened to them, it can happen to #metoo.
.
.
.
.

#metoo #metoomovement  #metooindia

text:
women are a tailored version of human beings and men are the untailored version
of it.
that is why they stereotype for boys to have messy rooms and girls to have neater ones, that is why girls are always all time expected to cut out clean.
no feminist move is a wrong move. a common argument made by both feminists and non-feminists alike. 
if 2017 feminists demand to have their tities out in open what's so
wrong about it if men have been doing it for ages. no it's not that we want what men already have. its that
this is a humanly feasible thing and because of our gender we are deprived of it.
why most men are angered from feminism, is because for the first time someone is asking them to tailor their
behaviour accordingly, against their will, and that's again something women have been brought up with so we know
the feeling but men can't take that kind of treatment because they have always been privileged in that sort
of way.
when you go to look into how deep patriarchy is instill in human lives, you might actually get stuck in the swamp of it all. but we must, we must dig deep and look to make the necessary changes.

text:
what constitutes workplace bullying?
bullying isn’t defined in the same way as harassment. primarily, it’s not against the law. bullying tends to be defined as repeated acts of intimidation, hostility and humiliation. but regardless of the legalities, bullying is as devastating to the individual as harassment.
what form does bullying take?
it can include:
verbal abuse, offensive comments
humiliating or ridiculing an individual and belittling their efforts in front of others
deliberate exclusion from conversations, meetings, social events
withholding information that a person needs to fulfil their role
pranks, practical jokes, initiation ceremonies
physical abuse
rifling through, hiding or damaging personal property.  #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
still surreal when i see photos like this of me on big international stages to think that just 4 years ago, i was a corporate executive who had no clue how radically my life was about to be changed. 💥

my life was turned upside down by my high stakes #metoo case at the end of 2014, but what emerged from the ashes of that has been so beautiful! 💥

i got deeply connected to my true purposes in life - to connect humans the world over in meaningful ways, to act as a conduit for social and venture capital, to give voice, agency and access to the marginalized and underrepresented, to facilitate healing from trauma and to help as many humans as possible feel genuinely seen, heard, loved and accepted. 💥

what an honor it was today to present at the southstart innovation conference in adelaide, south australia on the importance of tending to entrepreneurs’ mental health.  hope my message had positive impact on the people who heard it. 🇦🇺🇺🇸

text: if you really want to cause a stir at the family table this thanksgiving, don’t bother with the midterms, gun control, reproductive rights or #metoo. just say you don’t like turkey. for the last 90 years or so, we have been living in an era of poultry correctness. according to the national turkey federation (a.k.a big turkey), the rate of turkey consumption in the united states is roughly 5.3 billion pounds a year, with 45 million poor avian souls eaten over the holidays. this kind of popularity is hard to argue with. for dissenters, the tyranny of turkey is real — even though it’s an ordeal to prepare, and most of us know it’s really all about the sides. 🍗here are some #tbt turkey photos from @nytarchives throughout the decades. 🦃| 📸: patrick a. burns; marilynn k. yee; culver pictures; associated press; eddie hausner

text:
las víctimas del pastor lee jaerock, de 75 años, “eran incapaces de oponer resistencia, pues estaban sometidas a la autoridad religiosa absoluta del acusado”, subrayó el juez chung moon-sung ante el tribunal del distrito central de seúl.
la devoción religiosa puede ser muy fuerte en corea del sur, donde el 44% de los habitantes se declaran creyentes.
.
la mayoría de los fieles del país pertenecen a iglesias reconocidas, a menudo ricas y poderosas, frecuentadas por decenas de miles de fieles que no dudan en donar hasta el 10% de sus ingresos.
.
pero también hay muchas iglesias marginales, algunas de las cuales estuvieron implicadas en casos de malversación, coacción, “lavado de cerebro”, manipulación de fieles y otras actividades asociadas a prácticas sectarias.
.
lee jaerock fundó la iglesia de manmin, de inspiración protestante, en guro, un barrio pobre de seúl, en 1982. empezó con 12 fieles pero en la actualidad su iglesia afirma tener 130.000.
.
cuenta con una gran sede, un lujoso auditorio y su página web destaca el gran número de milagros que en ella se han obrado.
.
a raíz de las revelaciones del movimiento #metoo, que llegó también a corea del sur, tres fieles denunciaron este año al líder religioso, que las convocó en su casa y las forzó a tener relaciones sexuales.

text:
oh give thanks unto the lord for he is good for his mercies endureth forever. thank you for allowing us to see another thanksgiving day. thank you for the doors you've opened this week. thank you for the favor you've shown us on this week. thank you for lifting up a standard when the enemy came in like a flood. lord, we thank you for the victory. thank you for the battles that we've won and the battles we've lost. you are our sovereign god. thank you for your blood that has never lost its power. thank you for the storms you brought us through. if we never had problems, we wouldn't know that you, god, could solve them. we wouldn't know what faith in you could do. thank you for your hand of protection. bless everyone that has been praying with us thus far. bless their families, their finances, health, and their lives. bless this day.  help us to be grateful for all that we have. in the mighty name of jesus we pray. amen.
.
.

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text: you don’t have to call out your relatives if doing so will put you or anyone else in danger. if someone has people who will listen and not hurt them or anyone else, then that’s one thing and of course we should challenge racism, misogyny, xenophobia, fascism, and all the other very messed up stuff. but i keep running into people who out of guilt and trying to do good by calling out family members are putting themselves (or other loved ones who might be targeted after everyone has left) in danger, because of the mandate we’re hearing to speak up to our families on these holidays. again, if we can, we should! but i also think that this mandate is coming from a very privileged place; that the people who make a blanket call for it perhaps are not understanding what many people have been through in their families. for many, just being around family has fallout. please keep in mind, for example, how many women have families who have refused to believe them that a family member has sexually assaulted or abused them, or who believe but have done nothing about it. for someone facing that, calling someone out may set of a crash into dangerous depression, dorsal vagal collapse, or other debilitating responses that are outside of conscious control. if calling someone out may spark abuse or rage or painful re-igniting of past or present trauma, abuse, neglect, rejection, or pain, then please know you get to chose not to do it. maybe your energy is better spent where it will really do some good, and without putting you in danger. ***or maybe you and the other people around who are awake can decide who the least vulnerable person present is, and that person can be the one ready to call it out.*** but sometimes just getting through the day takes the whole energy. also, you don’t have to go at all if you don’t want to. also, these people on the side of the fascists are 100% always spoiling for a fight, and our words are not going to impact them at all in that setting. so take care. take your words and energy where it will matter. you are not the sacrificial offering. or if you are, take your offering where it will actually matter.

text:
the swedish hacker-cum-vigilante #lisbethsalander aka #thegirlwiththedragontattoo, has been the focus of a number of novels & film’s thus far, a series which has outlived its original creator #stieglarsson & finds the first novel not to be penned by larsson now the basis of the latest iteration of the character, played once again by a different actor… ranking up there with spiderman & sherlock holmes in the recasting stakes, 3 versions in a decade thus far, with woman of the moment #clarefoy the latest actress to take on the grungy titular character.
salander is an interesting creation, certainly in these times of #metoo & the like, a powerful central female icon in a universe that sees almost all the male characters as either powerful yet abusive or weak & very much reliant of salander as their saviour, the one exception to a degree being her hacker accomplice & aide”plague” who very much takes on a sidekick role this time, the dynamic akin to that of batman/alfred or blade/whistler, it’s interesting comparison to draw but one in which the route the studio & writers have taken with the franchise is now beholden to, “the girl” is no longer just an occasional avenging angel with her own issues but a superhero of sorts, indeed the first time we see salander “writing wrongs” the vigilante element that was previously in the periphery has now been well & truly pushed front & centre with the “hero” as she has now become being the film’s primary plotline.
efforts are made to shoe-horn in a more personal connection but it all feels rather unnecessary & desperate as if the film-makers were clinging at straws to be more than just a straightforward thriller, something past film’s always transcended the boundaries of, particularly #davidfinchers original dragon tattoo remake which was a stylistic marvel with a rather nasty edge & a labyrinthine plot that pulled you in, the male characters were more than mere stereotypes as previously described, here they are nothing other than stereotypes, thinly written ciphers with mikael blomkvist particularly badly served, played last time in a brilliantly vulnerable turn by #danialcraig here his replacement  #sverrirgudnason has

text:
it’s been an incredibly difficult 354 days and i am thankful every single day for the amazing humans that have helped me get back to myself and made sure that i got through these difficult days. in the spirit of thanksgiving, i want to focus on how much i am thankful for all of the amazing humans that have stood by my side after being sexually assaulted. everyone has made a tremendous difference in my life and i don’t want to speculate what even would be my life without every single one of you. and y’all know who you are. you have made a difference in my life for the better, particularly over the last year, and i will never forget every single one of you that has helped me so so so much every single day. today i am especially thankful for you. 
sy, md, rf, om, mt, st, kl: y’all were there from the beginning and continue to be there for me today and i’m so thankful for y’all.
hw, nt, nf, mt: my squad from the other side of the border. y’all have been so so so supportive from hundreds of miles and time zones away. i appreciate the unconditional support for me and the advice that all of you gave me all the time as well. 
js, kk, mb, mt: you were all there for me through the summer. you all have done so much for me and i am thankful for each of you every day.
mt, st, jm: y’all give me confidence every single day that i am doing really well in life and that you’d fight anyone for me. you guys are beyond supportive of everything in my life and i’d be lost without you three. you are the three that i want to run to with anything that i accomplished in life or when things are hard or when i need advice. you have each been so supportive throughout all of the processes that i am looking at. i am so thankful that you have all been there for me on the best days and the worst days and every single day in between. 
i am also so thankful for my fam. they have been supportive in every way that they knew how to. i wish i could be with them today.
i am so thankful for everyone that has been beyond supportive for me. i could not have come all of this way without every single one of you. 💕

sy, md, rf, om, mt, st, kl: y’all were there from the beginning and continue to be there for me today and i’m so thankful for y’all.
hw, nt, nf, mt: my squad from the other side of the border. y’all have been so so so suppoive from hundreds of miles and time zones away. i appreciate the unconditional suppo for me and the advice that all of you gave me all the time as well. 
js, kk, mb, mt: you were all there for me through the summer. you all have done so much for me and i am thankful for each of you every day.
mt, st, jm: y’all give me confidence every single day that i am doing really well in life and that you’d fight anyone for me. you guys are beyond suppoive of everything in my life and i’d be lost without you three. you are the three that i want to run to with anything that i accomplished in life or when things are hard or when i need advice. you have each been so suppoive throughout all of the processes that i am looking at. i am so thankful that you have all been there for me on the best days and the worst days and every single day in between. 
i am also so thankful for my fam. they have been suppoive in every way that they knew how to. i wish i could be with them today.
i am so thankful for everyone that has been beyond suppoive for me. i could not have come all of this way without every single one of you. 💕
